This project aims to predict whether a person's credit card application will be approved based on various demographic and financial features. The notebook includes data preprocessing, exploratory data analysis (EDA), model training, and evaluation.

##  Project Structure

- `credit_card_approval.ipynb`: Jupyter notebook containing all code for data cleaning, EDA, model building, and evaluation.

##  Features

- Data preprocessing and handling of missing values
- Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA) with visualizations
- Encoding of categorical features
- Model training using algorithms like:
  - Logistic Regression
  - Decision Tree / Random Forest
  - Support Vector Machine (SVM)
- Evaluation metrics such as Accuracy, Precision, Recall, F1-score, and ROC-AUC

##  Technologies Used

- Python
- Pandas, NumPy
- Matplotlib, Seaborn
- Scikit-learn

##  Data

- The dataset includes personal and financial attributes such as:
  - Age
  - Job
  - Credit score
  - Savings
  - Income
  - Previous default status, etc.

##  How to Use

1. Clone this repository.
2. Open the `credit_card_approval.ipynb` file using Jupyter Notebook or any compatible environment.
3. Run the cells in sequence to process the data and train the models.
4. Review model performance and insights at the end of the notebook.
